Judge Hughes in\ncircuit court hei quashed the tem\nporary writ of prohibition issued to\n[rive 10 days ({1 1^4 the Plunkett fr.ction of the demoera\n3-4 62 V&'i May I (ic party here restraining the couu'y\nnly 5 8,. -.\u2022I.. hudltor from placing tlio McDo :.,.d\nr''\n-I'uo.M rue ii li: u.d.\n41 nominal May In Marc*, as majority democrats.\nWithout going into the merits of\n5S 61 med- which faction constituted the major\nity, the court'ii'eld that the, Plunkett\nfaction was not properly in court.\nThis action probably will keep\nthem off the ticket and end the legal\nbattle that has ensued lor the past six\nNO CALL MADE\nON LAFOLLETTE\nMANAGER SHOUER SAYS HIS RJ8\nCENT MISSION TO WASHING\nTON\nWAS NOT TO OBTAIN\nI S A I\nHuron, S. D.\u2014The attention of II.\nC. Shober was today called to a pur\nported special from Washington,\nwhich appeared in the Argus-Leader\nof the ll)th lust., iu which it is al\nleged that Mr. Shober had'been in\nWashington to urge Senator LaFol\nletto to come to South Dakota to aid\ntho progressives in the present cam\npaign, and that he slipped in and slip\nped out without registering, etc. In\ncontenting upon the \"special\", Mr.\nShober made this jitatoment:\n\"The only truthful statement in tir\nspecial is that I was in Washington\ntho first, second and third of Febru\nary. My name appears in'the rigester\nof a prominent F. street hotel, where\nI remained during my stay 111 the city\nand paid my bill beforo leaving. 1\nwent to Washington 011 purely private\nbusiness and my expenses were paid\nby a Washington Insurance Company,\nthe meeting of the board of which I\nwent to attend. 1 did myself tho hon\nor to call upon each member of the\ndelegation from this state when in\nWashington, to pay my respects to\nmy successor in office and to spend a\nfew moments in greeting a few^score\nof my former assistants. But that is\nall personal and of 110 interest to tho\npeople of this state. I mention it sim\nply to show that tho correspondent\nlias as little regard for facts as has\nhe editor Sf that paper. I did not in\nany sense go to Washington on a po\nlitical mission. I did not call upon\nSenator LaFollette nor communicate\nwith him either directly or indirectly.\nFor years I have been a great admirer\nof the Wisconsin senator, and 1 have\ncounted it a great privilege to oc\ncasionally meet him during tho past\nfo\\y years and to give lilni an encour\nagiftg word. I have often gone half\nway across Our state to hear li is lec\ntures and I' think I have never'miss\ned an address that he lias given in\nSouth toakota when 1 have been in\nthe. state. I think I voice U12 senti\nment of all of our people, except man\nagers^ .when I say that we would rath\ner hear a discussion of the present\ncampaign issue by Senator LaFol\nlette lian by any other living man.\nMy ihforma&pn, however, is that the\nSenator is confined to his home by\nill health and that his duties In the\nsenate are greater than his strength.\"\nHow's This\nWo offer One Hundred Dollars Reward for any\ncms? of t'uturrb timt cnuuot be cured by Hall's\nCatarrh Cure.\nK. J. CHENEY CO., Toledo, O.\nWe, ihe uuilerslsDed, have known F. J.\nCheney for ibe lust 15 years, and believe blui\nperfectly honorable In a! I bushiest trauwactloos\nanY flnaselnlly able to carry out any obligations\nmade by his firm.\nNAT. BANK OF COMMERCE.\nToledo, Ohio.\nTUH's Catarrh Cure Is taken Internallr. acting\ndirectly upon the blood and inucuua surfaces of\nt....- ,yM\"m. Testimonial!* acnt free. Trice\nc. nu i.er tjtlle. Sohi by all Drugglata.\n...vf I).,11 r- aintb I*U1H Cm-\nJi*\nmm\nmiamm\nBessie Zetnlieka\nKntite llagen\nKranlc lva.stiu.-r\nThomas Rezuc\nFrancis Faliy\nFrank Schevur\nNick Kramer\nSollie Nolt\nLloyd McKeelian\nFarmer.\nMargaret Sclilodwciler\nWalter Fast\nJ'olin Hoiten\nWinne Baker\nDick Iiighstreet\nJohn Schuster\nMary Quinney\nLouis Boyies\nWill Pretzers\nHenry Kip.hu\nAdolph Priebe\nLizzie Brady\nSTANDING OF CUHTESTANTS\nII REPUBLICAN CONTEST\n